<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="175" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1122,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1302,1328]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons with median carina present and strongly marked. Pedicel with apical 2/3 yellow. Forewing with basal half dark brown and apical half light yellow with dark brown small areas. Periandrium bearing three preapical spines and aedeagus without spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="20" pageNumber="175" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1122,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1410,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Description</emphasis>
: Coloration. General body color light brown (
<figureCitation box="[866,952,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1295,1319]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.,: 84. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 85. Male head, anterior view; 86. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 87. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405047/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). Lateral carinae of the frons above lateral ocelli, median region of the frons, median region of the clypeus, apical 2/3 of pedicel, vertex, median region of pronotum and mesonotum and epimeron and episternum yellow. Forewing: basal half dark brown and apical half light yellow with dark brown small areas: diffuse dark brown transverse strip in the median region extending from the middle of the pterostigma to the CuA1 vein; 1/3 final of subcostal cell dark brown; ir, r-m, r-m, m-cu cross-vein dark brown; diffuse dark brown transverse band in the apical region that extends from the C1’ cell to the MP3 vein; diffuse dark brown transverse band in the apical region that extends from cell C3’ to cell C4’; narrow brown bands covering in MP1, MP2, MP3 and MP4 veins in wing apex; C5 cell predominantly dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1307,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 126–133. Wings of Bennarella species. 126. Bennarella bicoloripennis Muir; 127. Bennarella fusca Muir; 128. Bennarella guidai sp. nov.; 129. Bennarella henriquesi sp. nov.; 130. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.; 131. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.; 132. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.; 133. Bennarella xavieri sp. nov.. Abbreviations: A1, first anal vein; A2, second anal vein; CuA1; CuA2; CuP, Cubitus posterior; MP1, first media posterior branch; MP2, second media posterior branch; MP3, third media posterior branch; MP4, fourth media posterior branch; MP5, fifth media posterior branch; Pcu+A1, Postcubitus+first anal vein; Pcu, Postcubitus; RA, radius anterior branch; RP1, first radius posterior branch; RP2, second radius posterior branch; ScP, Subcosta posterior. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405067/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 131</figureCitation>
). Pterostigma yellow. Hindwing hyaline, yellowish with dark brown banner transverse rectangular in the median region of the apex. Legs yellow, except fore coxa and mid coxa dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[855,938,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1295,1319]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.,: 84. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 85. Male head, anterior view; 86. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 87. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405047/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). Abdomen dark brown, except upper half of sternite III, dorsal region of sternite IV, 2/3 of sternite V, posterior margin of sternite VI yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1358,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1295,1319]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.,: 84. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 85. Male head, anterior view; 86. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 87. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405047/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Figs 84, 87</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1122,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">
Head: frons with median carina present and strongly marked; lateral carina of frons strongly directed obliquely laterally (
<figureCitation box="[260,346,1842,1869]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1295,1319]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.,: 84. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 85. Male head, anterior view; 86. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 87. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405047/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
); vertex length approximately half the median length of the pronotum in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1422,1843,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1295,1319]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.,: 84. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 85. Male head, anterior view; 86. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 87. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405047/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
); pedicel approximately 4 times longer than wide and scape conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[950,1032,1878,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1295,1319]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.,: 84. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 85. Male head, anterior view; 86. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 87. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405047/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
). Thorax: pronotum and mesonotum with median longitudinal carina present but weakly marked; mesonotum with lateral longitudinal carina present and strongly marked (
<figureCitation box="[348,432,1951,1978]" captionStart="FIGURES 84–87" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1295,1319]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1435,181,1270]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 84–87. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.,: 84. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 85. Male head, anterior view; 86. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 87. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405047/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
). Forewing: m-cu cross-vein present (
<figureCitation box="[854,951,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 126–133. Wings of Bennarella species. 126. Bennarella bicoloripennis Muir; 127. Bennarella fusca Muir; 128. Bennarella guidai sp. nov.; 129. Bennarella henriquesi sp. nov.; 130. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.; 131. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.; 132. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.; 133. Bennarella xavieri sp. nov.. Abbreviations: A1, first anal vein; A2, second anal vein; CuA1; CuA2; CuP, Cubitus posterior; MP1, first media posterior branch; MP2, second media posterior branch; MP3, third media posterior branch; MP4, fourth media posterior branch; MP5, fifth media posterior branch; Pcu+A1, Postcubitus+first anal vein; Pcu, Postcubitus; RA, radius anterior branch; RP1, first radius posterior branch; RP2, second radius posterior branch; ScP, Subcosta posterior. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405067/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="175">Fig. 131</figureCitation>
). Legs: hind tibia with 6 apical spines; hind tarsus with 7+7 apical spines.
</paragraph>
