. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[456,481,1331,1355]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">87</emphasis>
. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 84 = 1 mm; 85–87 = 0.3 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1401,2040]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[392,523,1401,1427]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Figs 88–94</figureCitation>
). Pygofer subtriangular in lateral view, posterior margin with a rounded protuberance on each side in the middle region (
<figureCitation box="[595,679,1437,1463]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
); medioventral process of pygofer conspicuous in lateral view, with posterior margin triangular in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[660,746,1473,1499]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
). Gonostyli robust, wider in the apical half, with somewhat truncate apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[485,569,1509,1535]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
); inner margin slightly concave in the middle, rounded and divergent distally in dorsal and posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[478,608,1545,1571]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Figs 90, 92</figureCitation>
). Phallic complex (
<figureCitation box="[823,955,1545,1571]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Figs 93–94</figureCitation>
): periandrium almost straight bearing three preapical spines: one slender, elongate, rather straight spine, ventrally directed, inserted near apex with one short triangular lateral protuberance near base (S1), one slender, elongate, sinuous spine anteroventrally directed, inserted at apex (S2), and one shorter, slender, straight apical spine near apex (S3); aedeagus without spines, narrow at the base, enlarged in the median region and tapered at the apex. Anal tube concave ventrally; base of the anal tube subequal in length to anal tube extension in lateral view; anal tube extension abruptly curved ventrally at apex; apex rounded in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[455,586,1761,1787]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Figs 88–90</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="176" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1401,2040]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1797,1823]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named to honor Dr. José Albertino Rafael from the National Institute of Amazonian Research - INPA, Manaus, 
<collectingCountry box="[471,542,1833,1859]" name="Brazil" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, for his immense contribution to the knowledge to the Brazilian invertebrate fauna, and for collecting several specimens used in this work, including the 
<typeStatus box="[1002,1100,1869,1895]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="176" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1401,2040]" box="[199,669,1905,1932]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">
