<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1401,2040]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,409,1941,1967]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Viegas &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2022" authorityName="Viegas &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2022" box="[418,626,1941,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Bennarella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rafaeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[418,626,1941,1967]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Bennarella rafaeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[635,727,1941,1967]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[635,727,1941,1967]" pageId="21" pageNumber="176" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muir" authorityYear="1930" box="[1276,1399,1941,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Bennarella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1276,1399,1941,1967]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="176">Bennarella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by pedicel yellow in the apical 2/3, forewing light yellow with dark brown small areas in the apical half, dorsal region of sternite IV and 2/3 of sternite V yellow, periandrium bearing three spines and aedeagus without spines.
</paragraph>
